@Convicted
title: Johnson is removed from office
subtitle: Guilty votes: [+ yea_s_disp +]
view-if: senate_convicted = 1
on-arrival: president = "Wade" and president_party = "rep"

Andrew Johnson is convicted by the Senate and removed from the presidency. Under constitutional custom, Senate President Pro Tempore Benjamin Wade assumes the presidency to oversee the remainder of the term.

@Acquitted
title: Johnson survives impeachment
subtitle: Not Guilty votes: [+ nah_s_disp +]
view-if: senate_convicted = 0

The Senate falls one step short of removal. Andrew Johnson remains president, bruised, embittered, and openly hostile toward Congress.
